.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
The consistency semantics for data\-access operations using the set of
file handles created by one collective MPI_File_open is set by
collectively calling \fI\%MPI_File_set_atomicity\fP\&. All processes in the group
must pass identical values for \fIfh\fP and \fIflag.\fP If \fIflag\fP is \fItrue,\fP
atomic mode is set; if \fIflag\fP is \fIfalse,\fP nonatomic mode is set.
.sp
The default value on a call to MPI_File_open in Open MPI is \fItrue\fP for
jobs running on more than one node, \fIfalse\fP for jobs running on a single
SMP. For more information, see the MPI\-2 standard.
.SH ERRORS
.sp
